    Click on any release to be taken to the corresponding release on the Releases page.

    Key to symbols:

    • † after an issue number denotes the lack of an official catalogue number (e.g. it may be a marking on the record surface but not on the record label)
    • * after release denotes that only part of the take has been used for the issued title
    • ‡ indicates a release is not confirmed
    • ◊ indicates the first issue
    • # is added to a title to distinguish it from a different tune of the same name
    • * after a New DESOR number indicates it is not from the New DESOR or a correction sheet, but has been unofficially assigned elsewhere
    • External links have the following codes
      • (D): Discogs.com
      • (MB): MusicBrainz.org
      • (A): Amazon (US)
      • (AM): AllMusic
      • (AR): Archive.org
      • (F): Misc file
      • (S): Spotify
      • (T): Tidal
      • (YT): YouTube
      • (O): Other

Steven Lasker owns a 78 rpm test pressing containing the issued take, marked -1B. Therefore 4729j should be identified as take -1 and, consequently, unissued 4729f as take -2.

    Many thanks to Marv Goldberg for his attribution of Joe Van Loan to Joog Joog.

    B-Sharp Boston take -1 was issued in the USA in 1954 on Co PE-7. It had been released on Co(Sd) DS 1882 and Co(NL) DCH 25 in 1950; release dates are uncertain, but the Swedish record was likely released first.
